Pinus oocarpa

   [1702.jpg]
    Authority
      Family    Pinopsida:Pinaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 1702

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION
   A medium sized to tall evergreen tree reaching a height of 20-40 m. The
   trunk may reach a diameter of up to 50-60 cm.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial. The tree can withstand 3-6 or even 8 months of drought.
   COMMON NAMES
   Ocoti pine, Ocote, Ichtaj, Tocj, Chictaj.
   FURTHER INF
   Ocoti pine can be found at elevations from 400 to 2400 m. The tree
   occur naturally within the latitudinal range of 13-28Â°N. It can adapt
   to a vide range of sites from plains to valleys and steep slopes. The
   tree is termite resistant. Annual wood production potential is 10-40
   m3/ha.

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Webb D 1984 pp 221 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, PH, DRA, DEP, LIG, KTMP, USE]
   INSPIRE species 138 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, PH, DRA, DEP, LIG, USE]
   Serrano C 1978 pp 26-27 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, FER, PH, DRA, DEP]
   Morandini R 1961 pp 131-132 [TEMP, RAIN]
   Zabala N 1990 pp 132-134 [TEMP, RAIN, KTMP, DEP, FER, TEXT, DRA, USE]

